<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 98-12-08 - Releasing new cylinder head oil rail end plug.</stitle>
    <tsi id="tSI981208" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>98-12-08</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>May, 1998</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Engines</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Releasing new cylinder head oil rail end plug.</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>T 444E</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The cylinder head oil rail end plug, back up ring and O-Ring are no longer serviced separately. A
                    new service package containing a new end plug, back up ring and O-Ring has been created.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="insall" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Ordering Information:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="te98120801">Parts List
                    <xref refid="te98120801"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for the parts affected.
            </para>
            <table id="te98120801" frame="all">
                <title>Table 1 Parts List</title>
                <tgroup cols="3" colsep="0" rowsep="1">
                    <colspec colwidth="1.2in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="2.0in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="1.2in"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Part Number</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Description</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Displaced Part</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1 827 535 C91</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Cylinder Head Oil Rail End Plug Package (Consists of an end plug, back up ring and
                                    O-Ring.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry></entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Oil Rail End Plug</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1 818 186 C1</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry></entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Back Up Ring</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1 814 546 C1</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry></entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>O-Ring</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1 815 873 C1</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Perform the following steps when replacing the cylinder head oil rail end plug, refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f98120801">Back Up Ring And O-Ring Locations On Cylinder Head End Plug
                    <xref refid="f98120801"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard old end plug, back up ring and O-Ring from cylinder head.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a clean, dry, lint free cloth and brake cleaner, clean cylinder head internal
                    threads of dirt, loose particles and any foreign material. Dry thoroughly with a clean dry lint free
                    cloth.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>TO ASSURE A PROPER SEAL, BE SURE TO PREVENT ANY FOREIGN MATERIAL OR BRAKE CLEANER FROM GETTING
                        INTO THE OIL RAIL PASSAGE.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate new back up ring and new O-Ring with clean engine oil prior to installation
                    onto new end plug. Install back up ring and O-Ring onto end plug.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>TO ASSURE A PROPER SEAL, BE CAREFUL, NOT TO GET ENGINE OIL ONTO THREADS OF END PLUG.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a small bead of Loctite&#174; #277 around threads of the new end plug.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install end plug into cylinder head oil rail port. Tighten to the special torque value
                    of 81 Nm (60 lbf-ft)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>DO NOT START ENGINE FOR A MINIMUM OF ONE (1) HOUR. THIS ALLOWS THE LOCTITE&#174; TO CURE.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f98120801" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/EG7397.webp" type="webp" box="yes"/>
